column4: Hey guys, I have a TP-Link "TL-WN321G" wireless USB dongle on a Dell Latitude c600 notebook running Ubuntu 7.04.  The wireless works fine, but does not support WPA encryption.  WPA works in windows XP and is supported, so how can I make it work in ubuntu?
it's your only choice for wpa
wpasupplicant is already the newest version
